        "id": 2670964,
        "name": "Jeremy Holmes",
        "username": "Jeremy_Holmes",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jeremy_holmes/{size}/1146_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-07-06T05:29:02.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=1777893\"><strong>2012 Domaine d\u2019Eug\u00e9nie Vosne-Roman\u00e9e Le Clos d\u2019Eugenie</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Vosne-Roman\u00e9e (7/5/2019)</em><br>\nAbsolutely in the zone. Great nose of sandalwood, rose petal, beef stock, musk and red fruits. So silky in the mouth with good volume and exquisite balance and proportion. Quintessentially Vosne and a joy to drink.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=2412500\"><strong>2015 Fran\u00e7ois Raveneau Chablis 1er Cru Mont\u00e9e de Tonnerre</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, Chablis, Chablis 1er Cru (7/5/2019)</em><br>\nHighly complex nose of white peach, aniseed, preserved lemon, lavender and flint. It is rich, layered and powerful, giving plenty now but with a lot in reserve. The finish is so sappy and dense and length is impressive.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
