      {
        "id": 2671254,
        "name": "Nathan Smyth",
        "username": "Nathan_Smyth",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/8c91f0/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-07-06T19:24:39.000Z",
        "cooked": "<blockquote>\n<p>Is that even possible?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, I was imagining about 10,000 pages of bureaucratic paperwork and/or handing a bureaucrat a very large bag filled with many gazillions of euros [in untraceable bills] in order to get a vineyard name changed in Burgundy.</p>\n<p>I skimmed through the Wine Hog article, and it sounds like Bichot retained some IP rights to the old name of \u201cFrantin\u201d.</p>\n<p>Weird stuff.</p>\n<p>I\u2019d guess some lawyers earned a hefty payday when they wrote up all of those contracts [Engel, Frantin, Pinault &amp; Bichot].</p>",
